    <Content contentid="4260" contenttypeid="DNNG" desc="Dining">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>A particular highlight of a Seascape holiday is in-villa dining. Guests at Villa Seascape enjoy the expertise of their own very accomplished chef who is on hand to prepare breakfast, lunch and dinner daily.<br /><br />The villa provides complimentary daily breakfast as well as extensive restaurant-style priced menu of Indonesian, Asian and international dishes from poolside snacks, salads and light lunches to seafood barbecues and gourmet dinners – all served home-style either on the dining terrace or at the pool bar counter. The chef is happy to tailor meals to meet personal taste, special requests and dietary preferences, and the menu includes vegetarian options and children’s favourites. A stay is surely not complete without sampling some of Bali’s celebrated culinary specialities such as Babi Guling (roast spiced suckling pig) and Ayam Betutu (fragrant Balinese steamed chicken).<br /><br />We encourage you to plan meals a day in advance with the villa manager and chef, to allow time to shop for the freshest ingredients — many of which need to be ordered in from mainland Bali.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4261" contenttypeid="FAM" desc="Families">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Beautiful private villa + white-sand beach + tropical sunshine + charming staff makes Villa Seascape the perfect choice for families.  With generous indoor and outdoor living spaces, there’s plenty of room for kids to let off steam, as well as for parents to find peaceful corners of escape.<br /> <br />Families are sure to congregate around the pool, where young kids can enjoy the wide shallow ledge that runs the full length of the pool. Meals are fun when served at the sail-covered pool bar counter – no need to change out of a wet swimsuit!<br /><br />Kids of all ages will love the choice of entertainment zones within the villa. The netting-floored mezzanine is a super-cool space for sprawling in front of the TV suspended high above the living room, and the home cinema set-up in the media room, with huge drop-down screen is sure to be a hit.<br /><br />Food-wise, even the fussiest eater will be happy at Seascape. There’s a special children’s menu, and the chef is always happy to customise a dish or create special meals on request. There is of course the option to prepare baby and toddler meals yourself using the guest kitchen. The villa has a high chair, and we’re happy to source cots and baby baths for you upon request. (See full list of available <a href="http://cdn.elitehavens.com/docs/misc/eh_children_equipment.pdf" target="_blank">hire items</a>).<br /><br />The staff love having kids around and will make them very welcome. When you’re ready for adventures beyond the villa, there’s lots to do island-wide; check out our <a href="http://www.villaseascapelembongan.com/the-locale-cb/things-to-do.html" target="_blank">Things to do</a> page. And if parents would like to break free for an evening, or spend a kid-free afternoon exploring the island, the villa manager can arrange a babysitter (extra charges apply). </p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4262" contenttypeid="SPA" desc="Spa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Feel like a body scrub or massage? Just ask our staff to bring the spa to you! We can recommend deluxe treatments carried out in the privacy of your own villa by fully trained therapists from a reputable local spa. (Alternatively, stroll along the beach to Glo Spa at Sandy Bay Beach Club.) Here’s a sample of what’s on the menu (extra charges will apply):</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Balinese massage]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Release built up tension with a traditional Balinese massage. Using a combination of gentle stretches, acupressure and aromatherapy oils to stimulate the flow of blood, oxygen and energy around your body, you will feel totally relaxed in no time.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Foot reflexology]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Foot reflexology is a natural healing art based on the principle that there are reflexes in the feet which correspond to every part of the body. Through application of pressure on these reflexes tension is relieved and circulation improved leaving you feeling balanced.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Body scrub]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>A full body scrub will exfoliate and hydrate your skin leaving it soft and smooth. A rejuvenating scrub combines an abrasive material such as salt, coffee, rice bran or pecan hulls with essential oils to remove any impurities and make your skin glow.</p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Manicure/pedicure]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Our hands and feet work hard for us every day but rarely get the attention they deserve. Treat them to a manicure or pedicure, which usually comes with the added bonus of a quick hand or foot massage.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4263" contenttypeid="LCTN" desc="Location / Locale">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Villa Seascape occupies a commanding position on a small crescent beach on the south-western shore of Nusa Lembongan overlooking the Devil’s Tear, a local landmark where breakers crash along the limestone headland. The cove is home to a handful of prestigious villas, as well as the Sandy Bay Beach Club, which has a popular beachside restaurant and spa. While kids will enjoy playing on the sand, it’s not advisable to swim in the cove due to strong surf and currents. But Dream Beach, a lovely swimming beach, is just a 10-minute stroll away across the headland, while a 15-minute walk northwards brings you to the gentle waters and noted restaurants and bars of Mushroom Bay.</p>]]></Description>
