    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4265" contenttypeid="EHVD" desc="EH Villa Description">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Yearning for a sand-between-the-toes tropical island experience? Fantasising about an away-from-it-all beachfront home? Consider your dreams fulfilled at the sublime Villa Seascape on Nusa Lembongan, a small island off the southeast coast of Bali.</p><p>The dictionary defines the word seascape as a view of an expanse of sea. It’s the perfect name for this fabulous five-bedroom villa that enjoys a rare, absolute beachfront setting on the edge of small cove. Across the bay ocean rollers send dramatic spumes of spray high above the headland, Devil’s Tear; at night the lights of Sanur glimmer on Bali’s mainland 12 kilometres away across the Badung Straits.</p><p>Designed by Bali-based Italian architect Valentina Audrito, noted for her playful use of space, Villa Seascape offers an extraordinary variety of living areas, orbiting a double-height living room that spills onto a poolside entertainment terrace with access onto the beach. The interiors are thoroughly contemporary, with chic minimalist furniture in cool aqua colours resting on polished pebble floors, warmed by the creative use of bamboo, teakwood, terrazzo and shell. With the exception of the master bedroom pavilion, privately tucked away in the garden behind, every room in the villa enjoys spectacular ocean views.</p><p>This elegant villa promises magical experiences for families and groups of friends seeking luxury living and a laid-back vibe in a blissful beachfront setting. Daytime, recline in the shallows of the pool or on an oversized beanbag on the terrace, then convene at the pool bar for a light lunch served by the ever-attentive butler. Take an afternoon siesta on the suspended, netted-floor mezzanine, or draw the blackout curtains in the media room and languish on the gigantic floor cushion in front of a good film. Enjoy a dazzling sunset around the fire-pit or a cocktail at Sandy Bay Beach Club a minute’s walk along the beach, before tucking into a beachfront barbecue or gourmet meal prepared by the talented villa chef. After such a day, the supreme comfort of your suite and a blissful night’s sleep awaits.</p><p>Guests arriving in Bali late afternoon or evening should arrange overnight accommodation in Sanur and ferry transfers to Nusa Lembongan the following morning as sea crossings after 5pm are not recommended. A complimentary buggy will meet guests at Mushroom Bay on Nusa Lembongan for transfers to the villa.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="4267" contenttypeid="EHLD" desc="EH Layout Description">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>INDOOR LIVING:<br />- Huge double-height open-plan fan-cooled living room with a choice of seating areas, NID music system and Bose speakers.<br />- Guest kitchen with breakfast island, hob, fridge freezer and wine fridge.<br />- Dining terrace with seating for 10.<br />- Media room with 3m circular mattress piled high with cushions, projector with 260cm x 105cm retractable screen, sound bar, and digital movie library. (This room has an attached bathroom and can be converted to create a fifth bedroom).<br /><br />OUTDOOR LIVING:<br />- 15m x 4.9m pebble-lined swimming pool looking over the beach and ocean.<br />- Circular pebble-stone pool terrace with beanbag sun-loungers and seating built into a curved limestone wall.<br />- Sail-shaded poolside entertainment area with bar counter (can seat 10 for alfresco dining), sink and fridge.<br />- Beachfront sitting area with fire pit.<br />- Poolside shower and washroom.<br />- Private steps directly onto the beach.<br /></p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Indoor Living]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<ul><li>Huge double-height open-plan fan-cooled living room with a choice of seating areas, NID music system and Bose speakers.</li><li>Guest kitchen with breakfast island, hob, fridge freezer and wine fridge.</li><li>Dining terrace with seating for 10.</li><li>Media room with 3m circular mattress piled high with cushions, projector with 260cm x 105cm retractable screen, sound bar, and digital movie library. (This room has an attached bathroom and can be converted to create a fifth bedroom). </li></ul>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Outdoor Living]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<ul><li>15m x 4.9m pebble-lined swimming pool looking over the beach and ocean.</li><li>Circular pebble-stone pool terrace with beanbag sun-loungers and seating built into a curved limestone wall.</li><li>Sail-shaded poolside entertainment area with bar counter (can seat 10 for alfresco dining), sink and fridge.</li><li>Beachfront sitting area with fire pit.</li><li>Poolside shower and washroom.</li><li>Private steps directly onto the beach. </li></ul>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
